Package com.alexscode.utilities.dataset

Interface Dataset<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, java.lang.Iterable<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DatasetDiskBuffer, DatasetFromFile, DatasetFromStream, DatasetRAMBuffer, OnlineDataset
    public interface Dataset<E>
extends java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Interface abstraction the dataset concept A dataset is an ordered collection of things that can be streamed, converted to a list and iterated over. Warning: The minimum implementation is either the stream() method (preferred) or the getAsList() method. The more performant implementation probably require overriding all the methods
